I am an AWS Community Builder
okay coming from a restricted and highly
Orthodox background education was not an
easy to get option so it was my mother
who fought for my right to education and
made it possible
over a decade of experience I realized
that I should be upskilling myself then
I found out that AWS Cloud was making an
impact all around and I started learning
about AWS there by then I was introduced
into AWS user groups for my friend
berneshwari and then I joined the forums
because people from various background
were coming and giving their knowledge
use cases and expertise so from there I
learned a lot
from there the journey started I was
recording my cloud experiences with
respective to AWS in my own blog Cloud
goddess
apart from all this I have also been
with continuous contributions and
various other articles and different
forums I have been nominated and given
the title of AWS Community Builder two
years in a row now AWS scholarship was a
very big milestone in my life
for new developers I would say always do
your groundwork and take initiative
volunteering and attending technical
sessions will always create new doors of
opportunities
